body:
[Branch `ice` of the Amadeus repo](https://github.com/constellation-rs/amadeus/tree/ice) triggers an ICE. The ICE can be avoided by adding `#[inline(always)]` to the function identified in the error message. ```bash git clone https://github.com/constellation-rs/amadeus.git cd amadeus git checkout ice cargo +nightly-2020-06-10 test --features "aws" ``` ### Meta With `nightly-2019-10-15` two functions triggered this (see the most recent commit on the `ice` branch). With `nightly-2020-06-10` only one triggers it. My guess is inlining heuristics or similar have changed, making one of the functions inline thus avoiding triggering the ICE? ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: src/librustc_mir/monomorphize/collector.rs:766: cannot create local mono-item for DefId(112:77 ~ amadeus_aws[d447]::cloudfront[0]::{{impl}}[2]::from_line[0]) ```
